qtsixa (1.2.0-0ubuntu0+ppa1) lucid; urgency=low

  * Final 1.2.0 release:
    - Display a warning when the list of profiles was not found
    - Fixed crash when the list of profiles was not found
    - Also disable "Add New" and "Create New" buttons when no list found
    - Use pt_PT for pt_BR translations, for now
    - Special "--boot-yes" option fix for ArchLinux
    - Fixed sixad Makefile
    - Added a Makefile to QtSixA too (easy install for non-Debian systems)
    - Sixaxis configuration menu is more usable now
    - Warn user when using < 2.0 bluetooth dongle (Sixaxis incompatible)
    - Drop C++ code (python is good enough)
    - Added useful docs to the source tree

